# 18. もう一度あの景色を

Airi: *Sigh*...
Shizuku: Airi, are you still worried about Haruka?
Airi: Yeah. I can't help thinking about her.
Airi: Of all the idols I know, I think Haruka felt the most responsibility and took the most pride in her work.
Airi: Which means that her decision to quit would have been that much more painful for her.
Airi: Even I've had a hard time since I quit.
Airi: I know it was my own choice, but from waking up in the morning to going to sleep at night, I couldn't stop wondering whether I'd really made the right decision.
Airi: I couldn't even see how much I was worrying those around me.
Shizuku: Airi...
Shizuku: It was the same for me. All I could think about was how painful things were.
Shizuku: At first, I tried to be positive and think about the fact I'd have more time to myself without having to worry about what others thought, but it was no good.
Shizuku: I may have ended up an idol by accident, but somewhere along the way it became extremely important to me.
Shizuku: So when I quit, it felt like I'd lost a part of myself. It was really hard.
Shizuku: I wonder if Haruka feels the same way.
Airi: I wonder if there's anything we can do for her.
Airi: I know it's not our place to second guess a decision she struggled so hard to make, but still...
Shizuku: You're right. As fellow ex-idols, maybe there's something we can do for her.
Shizuku: Although I don't know what that might be...
Minori: *Huff*... *Huff*... Good morning!
Shizuku: O-Oh, good morning, Minori. Why are you so out of breath?
Minori: I'm going to need lots of stamina if I'm going to put on a show, so I ran 10km before practice!
Airi: What's with the sudden burst of enthusiasm? You were so down yesterday.
Airi: Wait, did you say show?
Minori: I'm going to put on a show for Haruka!
Airi & Shizuku: Really?
Shizuku: So that sea of blue glow sticks is a precious memory of Haruka's?
Minori: Right. And I think I can show it to her again by putting on a show in that other world.
Minori: That's why I decided to do this! Even if it only helps cheer her up a little...
Airi: But that view is only really visible from up on stage, right?
Airi: So, for her to see it, she'll have to be up there, which is the one thing she can't do. What are you going to do about that?
Shizuku: And if it really is a precious memory from her time as an idol, seeing it may be hard for her.
Minori: Well, I suppose that's true...
Haruka: I'm here to give everyone hope for a better tomorrow!
Haruka: There are some things that are impossible no matter how hard you try.
Minori: But Haruka no longer believes that tomorrow can be a better day.
Minori: It must be so painful for her to not look forward to the future like that.
Minori: If there's even a chance that it will help her move forward, I want her to see that view once more.
Minori: That light comes from the feelings of all the people Haruka gave hope to! I'm sure it will reach her!
Minori: Everyone's hope that Haruka can move forward, even if she's no longer an idol, will reach her!
Minori: I'm still thinking of a way to get her to come with me to the stage, but until I can, Haruka and I are both stuck in the present!
Minori: And if one show isn't enough to restore Haruka's faith, then I'll keep putting on shows until she's able to move on!
Shizuku: Minori...
Airi: Sigh... So in other words, you don't have a plan. At all. But you've always been like that, haven't you? You're so rash and unreasonable.
Shizuku: Hehe. You say that, but you've already decided to help, haven't you?
Airi: I guess so. I can't really blame her for something like this after what I did at your agency.
Airi: Minori, would you let us do this show with you?
Minori: Huh?
Shizuku: Yes, I'd love to help too. We were just wondering what we could do to help cheer up Haruka.
Shizuku: I'm finally able to think positively again thanks to what Airi did for me.
Shizuku: And since you're always thinking so much about Haruka, I believe that together, we might just be able to cheer her up.
Airi: Besides, we can't very well call ourselves idols if we don't cheer on someone with as much tenacity as you!
Minori: Thank you so much, Momoi! Hinomori!
Rin: I wonder how Minori and the others are doing. Maybe I should go and check in on them.
Miku: Hehe. I'm sure if we wait, they'll come visit soon. Oh, see! Here they come now!
Minori: Miku! Rin!
Rin: Oh! Airi and Shizuku are here too! It's been a while! How have you been?
Airi: Good. Thanks for everything, Rin. It's thanks to you that I'm finally able to try again.
Rin: Hehe. I'm so glad you're feeling better, Airi! Idols really do look their best when they smile♪
Shizuku: Hehe. You're right. Airi always seems so strange when she's feeling down.
Airi: Strange? Hey, even I get depressed sometimes, you know.
Minori: Miku! Rin! Guess what?! Momoi and Hinomori have decided to join the show to help cheer up Haruka!
Airi: We dropped by to see how big the stage was in order to help with practice.
Rin: In that case, why don't you stay here to practice? What do you think, Miku?
Miku: Yeah! This world was created from your feelings, after all. As long as we're not putting on a show, feel free to practice here as much as you like!
Shizuku: Really? That would be a huge help, right Minori?
Minori: Yeah! Thank you, Miku! Rin!
Airi: Stop! You're not moving your arms enough! You keep doing that during the second half of the song!
Airi: Think about making sure your feelings can reach all the way to the people in the back! Let's try that again!
Minori: Right!
Shizuku: Your pitch keeps changing a bit as well. That tends to happen when you tense up, so make sure to pay attention to your breathing, especially when you're nervous.
Shizuku: If you do that, your feelings will travel even further.
Minori: Right! Slow down my breathing... Relax my shoulders...
Rin: Wow! With Airi's and Shizuku's feelings working together like this, their performance is starting to shine brighter and brighter!
Miku: Hehe. I have a feeling this is going to be a great show.
Minori: I did it! That one felt perfect all the way through to the end!
Airi: Hold on. Let's check the recording to see. Yeah, looks great. This should be good enough to perform for Haruka.
Shizuku: Well done, Minori. I feel like we were setting the pace there toward the end, though. Sorry about that.
Minori: Don't worry about it. It's thanks to you two that I've come this far. Thank you so much!
Minori: All that's left is to reach Haruka!
Airi & Shizuku: Right!
